@29001 = ~That's it recruit. I have had enough. You can get away with a lot because of who you are, but this is a military campaign and there are limits!~
@29002 = ~You can't tell me what to do!~
@29003 = ~Yes, I CAN tell you what to do! You don't understand the value of the chain of command, and it is going to get someone killed. You have crossed the line over and over again, racking up violation after violation. At the same time, we are entering the most dangerous phase of this campaign. The Crusade could attack at any moment, and they will put this entire camp to the torch if they can. And if we survive that, we must attack a fortified castle.~
@29004 = ~I was scouting the castle! I saw a weak point in the walls, and -~
@29005 = ~We HAVE scouts, and you are not one of them! I don't care if you are skilled, or you obtained useful information. I cannot trust you to keep yourself and your squadmates safe in an engagement like this. I am sorry Skie, but your adventure is over. I am ordering you back to Baldur's Gate where you will be safe. I don't care if your father is a grand duke - I'll wager he will thank me for making this decision. Now pack up, and move out.~
@29006 = ~But it's not fair! <CHARNAME>, talk to him!~
@29007 = ~I said move out!~
@29008 = ~...Yes, sir.~
@29009 = ~You are making the right call. This is war, not a game.~
@29010 = ~You know, she is more capable than you realize.~
@29011 = ~I know Skie is more capable of handling herself than most of the recruits here. She is smart, has a flair for adventure, and got the best training money could buy. But she doesn't take orders seriously, and there are commanders in the Crusade who will easily see and exploit her weakness. Gods forbid they capture her - she is more of a liability than an asset right now. I hate to be so calculating but... this is a moment for hard choices.~
@29012 = ~Anyway, I can't stand around discussing it. I have things to do, and I am sure you do as well. See you around.~
