@22001 = ~Forgive us if we are disturbing you, my <PRO_LADYLORD>. My young colleague seems to be having some difficulty dealing with the stress of the situation. I am not sure how much he has been sleeping. Of course the situation does seem dire. But surely things are not as bad as he fears? Right? I confess, I begin to doubt myself...~ // thirri
@22002 = ~Not to worry. I am here to help. What do you mean 'having some difficulty?'~
@22003 = ~Stress? You are behind strong walls! Wait til the monsters are right in your face, then you'll know stress!~
@22004 = ~~
@22005 = ~The water... must not... water...~ // elandro initial
@22006 = ~The water? You mean the river? What about the water?~
@22007 = ~What are you talking about? You sound a bit crazy.~
@22008 = ~He has been walking around terrified, to the point of distraction, then he seems to dissociate, and move toward the edge of the fort, over here by the water. I would find his behavior fascinating if I didn't feel so bad for him. I have been trying to keep him calm, but it has been difficult. And sometimes it seems like his fear is making others around him more afraid.~
@22009 = ~Oh, er, sorry, my mind was wandering. I've been... I've been so fearful lately, I have been having a hard time staying focused.I just want to be away from this place! The water makes me so uneasy. Like it is pulling me in, even from here!~
@22010 = ~That is not a good idea. Maybe you should come with me inside the fort. You really should stay away from the river, I hear the waters are poisoned.~
@22011 = ~I tried to cross the river quickly - only meant to stop briefly in Bridgefort, and then move on as fast as possible. But then those damned crusaders showed up, and we have been trapped ever since!~
@22012 = ~I'm just a traveller! I just want to get away from this place! But those crusaders are acting like we are their enemies - they are going to slaughter us! Whenever I close my eyes it is all I can see, the slaughter!~
@22013 = ~Please, try to calm yourself. Getting worked up with fear will not help anyone. I intend to make sure the crusaders do not harm anyone. We will get through this, and then you can go on your way.~
@22014 = ~Calm down, man! Crying about your fears is not helping anyone. You need to get a grip on yourself before you start freaking people out.~
@22015 = ~There is no stopping it! Don't you see that? I've been running from it my whole life - the slaughter! But every time I stop, find peace, it returns! And now it's like - like waves crashing in my head! I can't get away because I'm stuck HERE!~
@22016 = ~Uh, are we still talking about the Crusade?~
@22017 = ~I will enter the water! Wait, no, I cannot - oh gods, there is no escape this time! They will breach the walls, bring the slaughter with them, and we will all die - ~
@22018 = ~Oh, no - what is happening to me?? I can't stop it -~
@22019 = ~~
@22020 = ~What is happening? What am I??~
@22041 = ~A feyr—a coagulation of magical energy and mortal fear manifesting in the physical realm. It seemed to spring from Elandro - or he turned into it? It is unclear how he could do such a thing; no spell was cast and no item was used to call forth such a being. It seemed to burst forth from within him.~
@22042 = ~A feyr is the inevitable consequence of a surfeit of magical energy combined with the unchecked fear of, say, a fort full of monkeys hiding in their own filth, trying to avoid an overwhelming force that seeks to destroy them. It is unclear how Elandro managed to turn into such a powerful creature; no spell was cast. It seemed to burst forth from within him.~
@22043 = ~The Fear

I've defeated the feyr that formed in the courtyard.

The magical energy enveloping Bridgefort combined with the anxieties and fears of those within it, somehow spawned a hideous monster known as a 'feyr,' directly from Elandro. It is not apparent what method was used to call forth such a creature - it did not seem voluntary, and Elendro did not apear to cast any spell.~
